info.author: Ole-Christoffer Granmo
info.description: Implements the Tsetlin Machine (https://arxiv.org/abs/1804.01508), Coalesced Tsetlin Machine (https://arxiv.org/abs/2108.07594), Convolutional Tsetlin Machine (https://arxiv.org/abs/1905.09688), Regression Tsetlin Machine (https://royalsocietypublishing.org/doi/full/10.1098/rsta.2019.0165), and Weighted Tsetlin Machine (https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/9316190), with support for continuous features (https://arxiv.org/abs/1905.04199), drop clause (https://arxiv.org/abs/2105.14506), Type III Feedback (to be published), focused negative sampling (https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/9923859), multi-task classifier (to be published), autoencoder (https://arxiv.org/abs/2301.00709), literal budget (to be published), incremental clause evaluation (to be published), and one-vs-one multi-class classifier (to be published). TMU is written in Python with wrappers for C and CUDA-based clause evaluation and updating.
